+---------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+------------+---------------------------------------------------------------------+
| equip\_availability\_postSwitch                   | What to assume about the availability of equipment after the switch (see `year\_equip\_availability\_switch`). The options for this are the same as `equip\_availability`.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               | String     | default                                                             |
+---------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+------------+---------------------------------------------------------------------+
| year\_equip\_availability\_switch                 | Year in which the assumption for `equip\_availability` changes (The change happens on 1st January of that year.)                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         | Integer    | 2100                                                                |
+---------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+------------+---------------------------------------------------------------------+
| Service\_Availability                             | List of services to be available. NB. This parameter is over-ridden if an argument is provided to the module initialiser.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                | List       | ['*']                                                               |
+---------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+------------+---------------------------------------------------------------------+
| policy\_name                                      | Name of priority policy adopted                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          | String     | Naive                                                               |
+---------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+------------+---------------------------------------------------------------------+
| year\_mode\_switch                                | Year in which mode switch is enforced                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    | Integer    | 2100                                                                |
+---------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+------------+---------------------------------------------------------------------+
| scale\_to\_effective\_capabilities                | In year in which mode switch takes place, will rescale available capabilities to match thosethat were effectively used (on average) in the past year if this is set to True. This way,we can approximate overtime and rushing of appts even in mode 2.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   | Boolean    | False                                                               |
+---------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+------------+---------------------------------------------------------------------+
| year\_cons\_availability\_switch                  | Year in which consumable availability switch is enforced. The change happenson 1st January of that year.)                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                | Integer    | 2100                                                                |
+---------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+------------+---------------------------------------------------------------------+
| year\_use\_funded\_or\_actual\_staffing\_switch   | Year in which switch for `use\_funded\_or\_actual\_staffing` is enforced. (The change happenson 1st January of that year.)                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               | Integer    | 2100                                                                |
+---------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+------------+---------------------------------------------------------------------+
| priority\_rank                                    | Data on the priority ranking of each of the Treatment\_IDs to be adopted by  the queueing system under different policies, where the lower the number the higher the priority, and on which categories of individuals classify for fast-tracking  for specific treatments                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                | Dictionary | :ref:`...<HealthSystem-priority_rank>`                              |
+---------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+------------+---------------------------------------------------------------------+
| HR\_scaling\_by\_level\_and\_officer\_type\_table | Factors by which capabilities of medical officer types at different levels will bescaled at the start of the year specified by `year\_HR\_scaling\_by\_level\_and\_officer\_type`. Thisserves to simulate a number of effects (e.g. absenteeism, boosting capabilities of specific medical cadres, etc). This is the imported from an Excel workbook: keys are the worksheet names and values are the worksheets in the format of pd.DataFrames. Additional scenarios can be added by adding worksheets to this workbook: the value of `HR\_scaling\_by\_level\_and\_officer\_type\_mode` indicates which sheet is used.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 | Dictionary | :ref:`...<HealthSystem-HR_scaling_by_level_and_officer_type_table>` |
+---------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+------------+---------------------------------------------------------------------+
| year\_HR\_scaling\_by\_level\_and\_officer\_type  | Year in which one-off constant HR scaling will take place. (The change happenson 1st January of that year.)                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              | Integer    | 2100                                                                |
+---------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+------------+---------------------------------------------------------------------+
| HR\_scaling\_by\_level\_and\_officer\_type\_mode  | Mode of HR scaling considered at the start of the simulation. This corresponds to the nameof the worksheet in `ResourceFile\_HR\_scaling\_by\_level\_and\_officer\_type.xlsx` that should be used. Options are: `default` (capabilities are scaled by a constaint factor of 1); `data` (factors informed by survey data); and, `custom` (user can freely set these factors as parameters in the analysis).                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               | String     | default                                                             |
+---------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+------------+---------------------------------------------------------------------+
| HR\_scaling\_by\_district\_table                  | Factors by which daily capabilities in different districts will bescaled at the start of the year specified by year\_HR\_scaling\_by\_district to simulate(e.g., through catastrophic event disrupting delivery of services in particular district(s)).This is the import of an Excel workbook: keys are the worksheet names and values are the worksheets in the format of pd.DataFrames. Additional scenarios can be added by adding worksheets to this workbook: the value of `HR\_scaling\_by\_district\_mode` indicates whichsheet is used.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         | Dictionary | :ref:`...<HealthSystem-HR_scaling_by_district_table>`               |
+---------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+------------+---------------------------------------------------------------------+
| year\_HR\_scaling\_by\_district                   | Year in which scaling of daily capabilities by district will take place. (The change happenson 1st January of that year.)                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                | Integer    | 2100                                                                |
+---------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+------------+---------------------------------------------------------------------+
| HR\_scaling\_by\_district\_mode                   | Mode of scaling of daily capabilities by district. This corresponds to the name of the worksheet in the file `ResourceFile\_HR\_scaling\_by\_district.xlsx`.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             | String     | default                                                             |
+---------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+------------+---------------------------------------------------------------------+
| yearly\_HR\_scaling                               | Factors by which HR capabilities are scaled. Each sheet specifies a 'mode' for dynamic HR scaling. The mode to use is determined by the parameter `yearly\_HR\_scaling\_mode`. Each sheet must have the same format, including the same column headers. On each sheet, the first row (for `2010`, when the simulation starts) specifies the initial configuration: `dynamic\_HR\_scaling\_factor` (float) is the factor by which all human resoucres capabilities and multiplied; `scale\_HR\_by\_popsize` (bool) specifies whether the capabilities should (also) grow by the factor by which the population has grown in the last year. Each subsequent row specifies a year where there should be a CHANGE in the configuration. If there are no further rows, then there is no change. But, for example, an additional row of the form ```2015, 1.05, TRUE``` would mean that on 1st January of 2015, 2016, 2017, ....(and the rest of the simulation), the capabilities would increase by the product of 1.05 and by the ratio of the population size to that in the year previous. | Dictionary | :ref:`...<HealthSystem-yearly_HR_scaling>`                          |
+---------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+------------+---------------------------------------------------------------------+
| yearly\_HR\_scaling\_mode                         | Specifies which of the policies in yearly\_HR\_scaling should be adopted. This corresponds toa worksheet of the file `ResourceFile\_dynamic\_HR\_scaling.xlsx`.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          | String     | no_scaling                                                          |
+---------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+------------+---------------------------------------------------------------------+
| tclose\_overwrite                                 | Decide whether to overwrite tclose variables assigned by disease modules                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 | Integer    | 0                                                                   |
+---------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+------------+---------------------------------------------------------------------+
| tclose\_days\_offset\_overwrite                   | Offset in days from topen at which tclose will be set by the healthsystem for all HSIsif tclose\_overwrite is set to True.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               | Integer    | 7                                                                   |
+---------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+------------+---------------------------------------------------------------------+
| mode\_appt\_constraints                           | Integer code in `{0, 1, 2}` determining mode of constraints with regards to officer numbers and time - 0: no constraints, all HSI events run with no squeeze factor, 1: elastic constraints, all HSI events run with squeeze factor, 2: hard constraints, only HSI events with no squeeze factor run. N.B. This parameter is over-ridden if an argument is provided to the module initialiser.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           | Integer    | 1                                                                   |
+---------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+------------+---------------------------------------------------------------------+
| mode\_appt\_constraints\_postSwitch               | Mode considered after a mode switch in year\_mode\_switch.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               | Integer    | 1                                                                   |
+---------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+------------+---------------------------------------------------------------------+
| cons\_availability\_postSwitch                    | Consumables availability after switch in `year\_cons\_availability\_switch`. Acceptable valuesare the same as those for Parameter `cons\_availability`.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  | String     | default                                                             |
+---------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+------------+---------------------------------------------------------------------+
| use\_funded\_or\_actual\_staffing\_postSwitch     | Staffing availability after switch in `year\_use\_funded\_or\_actual\_staffing\_switch`. Acceptable values are the same as those for Parameter `use\_funded\_or\_actual\_staffing`.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      | String     | funded_plus                                                         |
+---------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+------------+---------------------------------------------------------------------+

.. _Hiv-time_inf:

time_inf
--------

+--------+-------------------------+---------------+--------------+--------------+--------------+---------------------------------------------------------------------+--------------+--------------+--------------+---------------+---------------+---------------+---------------+---------------+---------------+---------------+
|   year |   probability_infection |   scaled_prob |   Unnamed: 3 |   Unnamed: 4 |   Unnamed: 5 | Distribution by CD4 count - HIV+ not on ART (15+) - (Male+Female)   | Unnamed: 7   | Unnamed: 8   | Unnamed: 9   | Unnamed: 10   | Unnamed: 11   | Unnamed: 12   | Unnamed: 13   |   Unnamed: 14 |   Unnamed: 15 |   Unnamed: 16 |

^^^^^^^^^^

Malaria
=======

+-----------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-----------+----------------------------------------+
| Name                                    | Description                                                                                                     | Type      | Value                                  |
+=========================================+=================================================================================================================+===========+========================================+
| itn\_district                           | data frame of ITN usage rates by district                                                                       | Dataframe | :ref:`...<Malaria-itn_district>`       |
+-----------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-----------+----------------------------------------+
| irs\_district                           | data frame of IRS usage rates by district                                                                       | Dataframe | :ref:`...<Malaria-irs_district>`       |
+-----------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-----------+----------------------------------------+
| sev\_symp\_prob                         | probabilities of each symptom for severe malaria cases                                                          | Dataframe | :ref:`...<Malaria-sev_symp_prob>`      |
+-----------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-----------+----------------------------------------+
| sensitivity\_rdt                        | Sensitivity of rdt                                                                                              | Real      | 0.95                                   |
+-----------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-----------+----------------------------------------+
| cfr                                     | case-fatality rate for severe malaria                                                                           | Real      | 0.15                                   |
+-----------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-----------+----------------------------------------+
| dur\_asym                               | duration (days) of asymptomatic malaria                                                                         | Real      | 110.0                                  |
+-----------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-----------+----------------------------------------+
| dur\_clin                               | duration (days) of clinical symptoms of malaria                                                                 | Real      | 5.0                                    |
+-----------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-----------+----------------------------------------+
| dur\_clin\_para                         | duration (days) of parasitaemia for clinical malaria cases                                                      | Real      | 195.0                                  |
+-----------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-----------+----------------------------------------+
| treatment\_adjustment                   | probability of death from severe malaria if on treatment                                                        | Real      | 0.5                                    |
+-----------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-----------+----------------------------------------+
| p\_sev\_anaemia\_preg                   | probability of severe anaemia in pregnant women with clinical malaria                                           | Real      | 0.075                                  |
+-----------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-----------+----------------------------------------+
| mortality\_adjust                       | adjustment of case-fatality rate to match WHO/MAP                                                               | Real      | 10.0                                   |
+-----------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-----------+----------------------------------------+
| data\_end                               | final year of ICL malaria model outputs, after 2018 = projections                                               | Real      | 2018.0                                 |
+-----------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-----------+----------------------------------------+
| irs\_rates\_boundary                    | threshold for indoor residual spraying coverage                                                                 | Real      | 0.5                                    |
+-----------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-----------+----------------------------------------+
| irs\_rates\_upper                       | indoor residual spraying high coverage                                                                          | Real      | 0.8                                    |
+-----------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-----------+----------------------------------------+
| irs\_rates\_lower                       | indoor residual spraying low coverage                                                                           | Real      | 0.0                                    |
+-----------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-----------+----------------------------------------+
| prob\_malaria\_case\_tests              | probability that a malaria case will have a scheduled rdt                                                       | Real      | 0.4                                    |
+-----------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-----------+----------------------------------------+
| itn                                     | projected future itn coverage                                                                                   | Real      | 0.6                                    |
+-----------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-----------+----------------------------------------+
| rdt\_testing\_rates                     | per capita rdt testing rate of general population                                                               | Dataframe | :ref:`...<Malaria-rdt_testing_rates>`  |
+-----------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-----------+----------------------------------------+
| scaling\_factor\_for\_rdt\_availability | scaling factor applied to the reports of rdt usage to compensate fornon-availability of rdts at some facilities | Real      | 1.2                                    |
+-----------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-----------+----------------------------------------+
| duration\_iptp\_protection\_weeks       | duration of protection against clinical malaria conferred by each dose of IPTp                                  | Real      | 6.0                                    |
+-----------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-----------+----------------------------------------+
| rr\_clinical\_malaria\_hiv\_under5      | relative risk of clinical malaria if HIV+ and aged under 5 years                                                | Real      | 1.7                                    |
+-----------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-----------+----------------------------------------+

| alternative\_ip\_anc\_quality                    | Signals within the analysis event that an alternative level of inpatient ANC quality has been determined following the events run                                                    | Boolean | False                                                                            |
+--------------------------------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+---------+----------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| ip\_anc\_availability\_probability               | Target probability of quality/consumables when analysis is being conducted - only applied if alternative\_ip\_anc\_quality is true                                                   | Real    | 0.9                                                                              |
+--------------------------------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+---------+----------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| sens\_analysis\_min                              | Signals within the analysis event and code that sensitivity analysis is being undertaken in which ANC is blocked from occurring                                                      | Boolean | False                                                                            |
+--------------------------------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+---------+----------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| sens\_analysis\_max                              | Signals within the analysis event and code that sensitivity analysis is being undertaken in which the maximum coverage of ANC is enforced                                            | Boolean | False                                                                            |
+--------------------------------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+---------+----------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
